\
We can see that the stratosphere is mostly heated by ozone\'92s absorption of solar radiation and cooled through the combined net longwave effect of \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\), ozone, and water vapor. So if \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) is increased throughout the atmosphere, more \\(\\text\{CO\}_2\\) in the stratosphere will lead to more cooling there.\
